summary: This document is an email chain from October 11, 2019, within the FBI's Violent Crime Section, discussing and approving travel for agents to conduct victim briefings and interviews in Florida related to the ongoing Epstein investigation. The travel is for agents to meet with victims in Miami, West Palm Beach, and Palm Coast.

persons.name: SA Young
persons.context: SA Young in NY is requesting approval for travel to Florida for victim briefings and interviews as part of the Epstein investigation.

events.title: Travel Approval for Epstein Victim Interviews
events.description: The FBI's Violent Crime Section approves travel for agents to travel to Florida the following week for victim briefings and interviews in Miami, West Palm Beach, and Palm Coast as part of the Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: The FBI was actively conducting victim briefings and interviews in Florida in October 2019 as part of the Epstein investigation.
Travel was approved for four agents to travel to Miami, and for two agents to travel to West Palm Beach and Palm Coast.
The estimated total cost for the investigative travel was $6,263.50.
The request and approval originated from the FBI's Violent Crime Section, Crimes Against Children and Human Trafficking Unit (CACHTU).
The document indicates coordinated investigative efforts between the FBI's New York office and the Violent Crime Section.
